This paper deals with the design of auctions, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and falls under the broader area of algorithmic mechanism design. The problem involves designing auctions that maximize revenue, which is a problem in optimization (cs.DS) and involves modeling bidders' valuations, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the concept of prior-free auctions, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT).
